00:32:12.560 --> 00:32:14.340
was made to entertain people.

00:32:14.340 --> 00:32:16.360
Not-- it's not
necessarily my idea

00:32:16.360 --> 00:32:18.490
of how a Mars mission
will probably work.

00:32:18.490 --> 00:32:21.410
I did it deliberately to evoke
those feelings of the Apollo

00:32:21.410 --> 00:32:22.070
era.

00:32:22.070 --> 00:32:25.970
And that excitement that every
reader-- everybody in the world

00:32:25.970 --> 00:32:28.720
has some sense, some connection
with the Apollo program,

00:32:28.720 --> 00:32:30.520
even if you were
born way afterward.

00:32:30.520 --> 00:32:34.360
And so this rather
shamelessly and cheesily

00:32:34.360 --> 00:32:35.920
pulled on those heart strings.

00:32:35.920 --> 00:32:38.070
Realistically, I think
a manned mission to Mars

00:32:38.070 --> 00:32:41.070
would be a large international
effort, like the International

00:32:41.070 --> 00:32:42.350
Space Station.

00:32:42.350 --> 00:32:45.325
I think it'd be us, European
Space Agency, the Russians,

00:32:45.325 --> 00:32:48.550
maybe even the
Chinese, JAXA for sure.

00:32:48.550 --> 00:32:53.460
And it'll be this big
complicated space station

00:32:53.460 --> 00:32:55.170
basically that
they send to Mars.

00:32:55.170 --> 00:32:56.530
And it'll be like that.

00:32:56.530 --> 00:33:00.060
So that's my prediction for how
a manned Mars mission will go.

00:33:00.060 --> 00:33:04.090
And I also think that-- NASA
says they can do it by 2035.

00:33:04.090 --> 00:33:06.415
I believe they could if
they got enough funding,

00:33:06.415 --> 00:33:08.290
but I don't think they'll
get enough funding.

00:33:08.290 --> 00:33:11.630
I predict more on
the order of 2050ish.

00:33:11.630 --> 00:33:13.190
That's my guess.

00:33:13.190 --> 00:33:14.940
And then your other
question is, what do I

00:33:14.940 --> 00:33:16.820
feel about the future
space exploration.

00:33:16.820 --> 00:33:20.010
I think we're right at the
cusp of an awesome era,

00:33:20.010 --> 00:33:21.560
because now we're
finally starting

00:33:21.560 --> 00:33:24.260
to look at it from a commercial
and economic sense, instead

00:33:24.260 --> 00:33:27.090
of just a flags and
footprints kind of thing.

00:33:27.090 --> 00:33:29.500
And, so, we've got
companies like SpaceX

00:33:29.500 --> 00:33:30.820
driving the price down.

00:33:30.820 --> 00:33:33.950
I think the absolute
key to space exploration

00:33:33.950 --> 00:33:37.760
is driving the price down to get
a mass in the low earth orbit.

00:33:37.760 --> 00:33:41.755
Once you do that a commercial
industry will naturally evolve.

00:33:41.755 --> 00:33:44.360
And if you don't believe
me, let me ask you this.

00:33:44.360 --> 00:33:47.640
All of you, your engineers
mostly, probably, right?

00:33:47.640 --> 00:33:51.070
And, so, you make decent income,
but you're not billionaires,

00:33:51.070 --> 00:33:51.960
right?

00:33:51.960 --> 00:33:55.990
Would you pay $100,000
to spend a week in space?

00:33:55.990 --> 00:33:58.200
Raise your hand if you
would pay $100,000 to spend

00:33:58.200 --> 00:34:00.190
a week in a space hotel.

00:34:00.190 --> 00:34:00.820
All right.

00:34:00.820 --> 00:34:05.290
So this is about 30% of the
population of this room.

00:34:05.290 --> 00:34:09.230
If you could make it such that
middle class Americans could

00:34:09.230 --> 00:34:11.580
afford, as a once
in a lifetime event,

00:34:11.580 --> 00:34:15.719
to go into space for a week, you
would have effectively infinite

00:34:15.719 --> 00:34:16.900
demand.

00:34:16.900 --> 00:34:18.830
And then that's
when companies would

00:34:18.830 --> 00:34:21.590
start to come in, and
figure out the technology

00:34:21.590 --> 00:34:23.909
necessary to drive the price
down further and further

00:34:23.909 --> 00:34:25.260
and compete with each other.

00:34:25.260 --> 00:34:28.280
So it all starts with companies
like SpaceX and Boeing,

00:34:28.280 --> 00:34:32.409
and the commercial
programs that NASA's doing.

00:34:32.409 --> 00:34:34.449
And I think we're on our way.

00:34:34.449 --> 00:34:37.067
So I think it's going
to be pretty awesome.

