00:47:23.340 --> 00:47:26.731
And, so, after work I'm at home.

00:47:26.731 --> 00:47:33.300
[LAUGHTER]

00:47:33.300 --> 00:47:37.470
So, and I don't know.

00:47:37.470 --> 00:47:41.010
It's just-- the main thing
that motivated me and made

00:47:41.010 --> 00:47:42.924
it a priority for
me was releasing

00:47:42.924 --> 00:47:43.840
it chapter by chapter.

00:47:43.840 --> 00:47:46.320
I got feedback and
just constant reminders

00:47:46.320 --> 00:47:48.140
that people really
were reading it.

00:47:48.140 --> 00:47:49.890
Every time I'd
release a chapter,

00:47:49.890 --> 00:47:52.487
I'd get hundreds of emails
of people with feedback.

00:47:52.487 --> 00:47:54.570
And it just went, OK,
people are reading my stuff.

00:47:54.570 --> 00:47:57.220
And I think that's--
almost no writter--

00:47:57.220 --> 00:47:59.760
almost every writer
is driven by that.

00:47:59.760 --> 00:48:01.700
Not driven by like, I
want to make some money.

00:48:01.700 --> 00:48:03.033
I mean some of them are I guess.

00:48:03.033 --> 00:48:05.010
But the vast majority
of us are just like,

00:48:05.010 --> 00:48:06.410
people are reading this book.

00:48:06.410 --> 00:48:08.740
I created of a fictional world.

00:48:08.740 --> 00:48:11.510
And other people are
enjoying it and I love that.

00:48:11.510 --> 00:48:13.347
And so that'll help motivate me.

